task.summary: Default task

handling for parts
- added handler and tests for part-names - work toward issue #186

handling for clefs and keys
- added handler and tests for clefs and keys - these work pretty much the same way and could be merged into the same method, but only for simplification I'll leave as is for now - work toward issue #186

handling for meters, tests for meters and tempos
work toward issue #186

handling for tempos
work toward issue #186

bibliography handler
- added handling for movement title and creator tags - also added "predictive" handling of credit-words tags based on justification and vertical alignment - this is because MuseScore uses credit-words for all text rather than putting title and creator in the right places... - work toward issue #186

added collator
- added a method which takes the part dictionary which contains data about specific parts, including their names, clefs, keys and transpositions, and puts them into the data dict - need to test the parser against a real xml file and then this can be closed - work toward issue #186

added testcase/tests for testcase + other
- added testcase which tests bibliography (title, composer, lyricist), tempo, time sig, key sig, instruments -created a testclass for this testcase and made sure all tests pass - added handling for beat-unit-dot - added handling for lyricist and removed credit-words section as I notice latest version of MuseScore uses the right tags, not credit-words. Hoping sibelius does the same.

added lyricist support
- added new table to database (lyricists): not sure if this is entirely useful, may be better to have a creators table which combines both lyricist and composer. For now doesn't make a massive diff - added tests for add method - work toward issue #191

added search by lyricist
- added helper method to find lyricist id and method to find pieces by that lyricist - issue fix #191
issue fix #190, removed superfluous octave column

added a second testcase
- added testcase2.xml to test beat=beat metronome markings - added unit tests and confirmed they pass - issue fix #186

implemented parser at manager level
- implemented parsing in parseNewFiles + tested this works with some new unit tests and by copying one of the testcases into the manager folder - removed old testcase because this caused the thing to fall over: should *probably* do some kind of error catching for this in future. - work toward issue #189

implemented delete method option 1
- implemented deletePiece method which obliterates all data about a piece - intend to change this so that it archives it instead, and then when the user refreshes the collection we can ask whether it should be deleted if the piece re-emerges. - work toward issue #192

implemented delete method option 2
- implemented archivePiece which doesn't delete everything - just changes archived to be a 1 - kept remove method in case a user wants to completely delete previous data - work toward issue #192

issue fix #192
- implemented archiving system in every method which ignores any pieces which are archived - this can be switched to searching only the archives by putting in the param at the end archived=1

implemented archiving at manager level
- added method call in handleOldFiles - issue fix #189

implemented refresh method
- added method calls for unzipping and xml handling to refresh method - issue fix #65

added method to data layer
- added find by modularity - added unit test to confirm functionality

added get by all pieces method
- added a method which gets all pieces which are in any key - this also checks instruments those keys are applied to for transpositions: if these are applied it will ignore the result - work toward issue #183

further "get-all" methods in data layer
- added methods for clef/tempo/meter/composer/lyricist - also added tests + made it so that all titles, composer names and lyricists are lower case: this is so that they are more likely to match to other composers/lyricists etc. - work toward issue #183

get-all method for instruments
- added method to get all parts related by instrument to data layer - also included handling where instruments are transposed: this could be improved a bit, will explain in an issue - work toward issue #186

changed data layer getter methods
- changed all querying for playlists methods so that they don't collect results unless there are more than 1 unique files with that attribute - implemented data layer call methods in playlists and again checked length of each result before adding to the returned playlist dictionary - issue fix #183
bug fix: comma added to usages of archived so that SQLIte doesn't complain
addition to issue #191: added lyricist to output from querying data layer
refactoring to dict names in playlister data methods

cleanup of app file
- moved some of the main window stuff into a new method - added music manager to parent application which will handle talking to each window + data links: this makes sure any popup boxes can get access to data without talking to the main app window. - work toward issue #67

connected first widget
- issue fix #199: connected the first listbox to it's data source and implemented sorting according to drop down change. Will need some testing on files containing composers/lyricists etc.

connected listbox to appropriate callback
- gave each qListWidget an item relating to it's filename - connected each item to a callback when it's double clicked - created a method in the parent application which will handle rendering and give the main window a pdf to play with - work toward issue #69

finished connecting startup box to callbacks
- connected select folder button to a folder browser, which upon return/selection of a valid folder will open up the main GUI - created a new method which will save the folder to a list which then gets serialised to a file (.collections) - connected the listbox to the left of the gui to the items from this file - connected the callbacks from each listbox item to open that folder upon double clicking the item - issue fix #200

created new playlist box and made some bug fixes
- upon testing a few things bugs were encountered with for example, refresh buttons so fixed those - added new playlist dialog UI design, need to connect this with code (work toward issue #75)

linked selection to callback

got poppler working: issue fix #202
- poppler fixed by installing poppler from source rather than from brew: this ensured that the proper links were created - installed python-poppler lib using pip, and then had pycharm install the same lib on the homebrew pythonpackage manager. - this now loads pdfs reasonably quickly, thow rendering should happen on a separate thread so that we can display a "loading" gif
